The paper deals with complexity and algebraic geometry, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on tensors and orbit closures suggests that it could also belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The mention of geometric complexity theory (GCT) suggests that it could belong to cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
